sentences: Jay DeMarcus (born Stanley Wayne DeMarcus Jr.; on April 26, 1971) is an American bassist, vocalist, pianist, record producer and songwriter.
DeMarcus attended Lee College in Cleveland, Tennessee, from 1990 to 1992.
DeMarcus co-founded the contemporary Christian music group East to West and moved to Nashville, Tennessee, in 1993.

In 1997, after East to West disbanded, he called his second cousin, Gary LeVox, with whom he played when they were younger, and convinced him to come to Nashville and provide some harmonies on Michael English's album Gospel, which he was producing.
He produced the 2006 release for the band Chicago titled, Chicago XXX.
On March 4, 2010, DeMarcus and his band mates were guest stars on CSI: Crime Scene Investigation, appearing as themselves.
In October 2018, DeMarcus founded the label Red Street Records, an independent Christian music label.
On May 15, 2004, DeMarcus married Allison Alderson  a former beauty queen who has held the titles Miss Tennessee 1999 and Miss Tennessee USA 2002.
